post_text:
This is just a friendly reminder that your student’s bus information can be found on OnCourse. Please remember to check your bus stop, bus number, and pickup time the day before school, as times are changing daily due to new enrollments, disenrollments, address changes, etc. and students are added or dropped from bus routes.

Please be at your scheduled stop ten minutes prior to your listed pick up time. For the first two weeks of school, we even recommend being at your stop 15 or 20 minutes prior, as the first two weeks are always a bit hectic with the start to a new school year.

Masks are mandatory and must be worn on the bus at all times. A student will not be allowed on the bus without a mask.

Thank you!

Attention all Pinelands Regional School District, Little Egg Harbor School District, Tuckerton Elementary School and Eagleswood Elementary School parents:

The online free/reduced lunch application portal is now open.
https://mealapp.lunchtimesoftware.net/

Please remember, only one application is needed per family as long as your children attend one of these schools. Please also be sure you included all household members, including out of district students and non-school aged children. If you have any questions or are new to the district or are unable to submit an online application, please contact Sarah O'Toole at sotoole@lehsd.org.

*Your prior year eligibility will be available at the beginning of the school year, but is set to expire on October 20, 2020.
**A PDF version and instructions can be found on the school website. You may print and mail it to:
Little Egg Harbor School District
Attn: Sarah O'Toole
307 Frog Pond Rd.
Little Egg Harbor, NJ 08087

ECC - Jackie Harned jharned@lehsd.org

Good Afternoon Parents,

If we have loaned your child or children a device to borrow during the time of Remote Learning and you have not returned them, the following message is for you.

The district is collecting these devices so that they can be professionally cleaned June 29 and 30 (this coming Monday and Tuesday). Please let us know if you can drop off the device at Frog Pond tomorrow. If you need us to pick up the device from your home, please email distancelearning@lehsd.org

We will be happy to pick them up!

We will be reissuing devices to ESY participants.

Thank you for your help and cooperation!

Good Morning!
Food distribution will begin at 10:30 tomorrow until noon at the high school. With the weather getting hot we are gonna make the sandwiches and freeze them so they stay nice. If they are still frozen either keep them in the freezer and pull them out in the morning or eat them up. Also looking into changing the menu up for some more variety. ￼Things like pizza bagel bites and cheese quesadillas. I’m running into shortages on certain items like the peanut butter and jelly uncrustables ￼so will just be rolling with what we can. It’s looking more and more like we will be able to do this all summer. We sincerely hope this helps.
All students are eligible

post_text:
Good Afternoon,

We know that many families in our community have been affected by the current lack of work due to business closures. If your family has been directly affected, you may be eligible for a change in our meal program status. If you are on unemployment or your salary has been reduced: this IS considered a change of economic circumstances and you are eligible to reapply for free/reduced meals for your students. Additionally, you may be eligible to receive additional state aid that is currently being approved. Please visit your school's website where you can find the link to apply for free/reduced lunches online. We ask that you do not hesitate. Please submit your application not later than Wednesday, May 20th.

Stay Well!

Governor Murphy has made the determination to continue with remote instruction through the remainder of the school year. Furthermore, he stated that additional guidance will be coming out regarding graduation/promotion ceremonies and E.S.Y. We will be waiting for his guidance prior to making any final plans for graduation or 6th-grade promotion. Multiple plans have been created and are ready to go.

The administration will begin to create plans for:
-Students to obtain their belongings from school
-Teachers to gather their belongings from school
-Collecting technology
-ESY: remote if necessary
-The 2020-2021 opening of school

Thank you and stay well.
Melissa McCooley

FrogPond Principal is feeling grateful.
May 1 at 8:43 AM ·

Today, we would be celebrating these unsung heroes that come to school every day, bright and early, to serve our children breakfast and lunch with a smile. We have the best lunch staff in the world!

Let's not forget, when school closures rocked our world, these professional and caring human beings, came to work in the midst of a crisis, to feed our families, with smiles on their faces and joy in their hearts. EVERY brown bag was personalized with a positive message, telling us...we will get through this!

Please reply and share your comments about these wonderful people!

post_text: Mr. Henderson, Mrs. Henderson, and I started setting up the generous donations of candy from CVS at 8:00AM. Community members were in line at that point. At 8:25AM, when the line was backed-up to Nugentown Road, we decided to start distributing. Each family only took what they needed and we ran out a little after 9AM. Candy was also delivered to families that reached out and did not have a vehicle. In the future, we will clearly state that we will distribute until we run out. Thank you to Mr. & Mrs. Henderson for arranging this! Thank you to the LEH Officer helping with traffic! Happy Easter everyone!!!

post_text:
March 20, 2020

L.E.H. & P.R.S.D. Families,

As you are well aware, the COVID-19 pandemic continues to escalate in our area. To ensure the safety and well being of our staff, students, and community the Little Egg Harbor and Pinelands School Districts will remain closed through spring recess. The tentative date our schools will reopen is April 20, 2020. Please note, during spring recess (April 10th-April 19th) food will not be available to families. Refer to the Pinelands website, Food Finder link for resources to assist with feeding your family. Lastly, teachers will not be providing lessons or assistance during the spring recess time period. Students should use that time to catch up on any incomplete work.

Additionally, if you need a Chromebook for your student, we are limiting loaner devices to one per family due to the limited number of devices available in both districts.

Thank you for your patience. Stay safe!

Dr. Melissa McCooley

Thank you to all our staff and students from Frog Pond Elementary School for your generosity during this busy holiday season! Thanks to all of you we have raised over $480 for David's Dream & Cancer Foundation

David's Dream & Believe Cancer Foundation is a 501(c)(3) non-profit that raises funds to provide financial assistance, wellness services and hope to New Jersey families affected by a cancer diagnosis!

Flyers will go home the end of the week to sign up for Generation Dream - Frog Pond Elementary our after school DDBCF Group!

Pinelands Regional School District will be hosting an important presentation regarding opioid abuse next Thursday, December 12th at 6:30pm in the High School Auditorium. Parents are invited and encouraged to attend with their junior high school and high school students.

George Street Playhouse will be presenting "ANYTOWN" a new musical about opioid abuse and its impact on teens and families.

Please note, this program is not for elementary school aged children. However, parents with students of all ages are welcome to attend.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

The children at GJM in the Kindergarten classes will be reading a book called The Mitten Tree by Candace Christiansen. The story was about a woman named Sarah who made mittens for all the children in the neighborhood who did not have mittens. The children in the story were very appreciative of Sarah's thoughtful act.

In keeping with the holiday spirit of giving, our classes would like to create a mitten tree at the GJM and Frog Pond Schools. We would like to collect new or gently used mittens, jackets, hats and scarves for the local families who do not have these items to keep them warm this winter. If you would like to donate items, please send them in with your child to put on the tree in their building. We will collect mittens and such until December 13th, 2019. If you have any questions, please contact Mrs. May at Lmay@lehsd.org.

Thank you for your kindness.

Sincerely,

The Kindergarten Teachers

post_text: Yesterday, World Kindness Day was celebrated in all of our schools! Frog Pond started a month-long quest to catch students being kind to others. If a student is caught being kind, they will get their picture taken in front of our "Be the 'I' in Kind" bulletin board. Their pictures will be displayed in school, and at the end of the month-long activity, we will create a video of all of our recognized students and share that with all of you! We have so many amazing students! Encourage them to be kind every day!
